<title>Open a Sort Specification or Dictionary File</title>
<context ID_FILE_OPEN />

<list ordered>
	<li>From within CSPro, click <image open_button.png /> on the toolbar; or from the <b>File</b> menu, select <b>Open</b>; or press <b>Ctrl+O</b>.</li>
	<li>From your Windows File Explorer, double-click on the sort specification file (*.ssf) or dictionary file (*.dcf) you want to open.</li>
</list>

If you have not created a sort specification file (.ssf) yet, you must first open the dictionary file which describes the data you want to sort. After making your sort selections, you can then save this information into a <link save_a_sort_specification_file.csdoc>save a sort specification file</link>.
